Frontend: Vue.js, Next.js 

Backend: PHP, Symphony, Laravel 

Microservices: AWS Lambda, Node.js, Python 

Cloud: AWS Cloud Services 

Points 

Code Generation  

Agent mode development (No Plan mode) 

Test cases generated by AI 

No manual test development 

GitHub Copilot plugin pointed to Claude (Enterprise license) 

Documentation  

Documentation generated by AI 

Code Review  

PR review board integrated in GitHub CI/CD pipeline 

Human review is negligible 

Duplicate code identification depends purely on review board (no centralized solution) 

JIRA AI  

Writes basic description elaboration 

Generates acceptance criteria 

Google Workspace with Gemini  

Daily standup meeting transcription 

Sprint-end analysis of transcriptions 

Emails, Slides, Docs, Sheets integration 

Solution discussions via prompts 

Creating presentations and documents 

Recent AI-Driven Feature Implementation 

Policy Score Feature: In the Compare Club dashboard, users can view their insurance policy list with a suitability score. If the score is 100%, the policy is suitable; if less, it needs review. The logic was generated by AI and implemented using AI-assisted development. 

Code Quality Observation 

Claude 4.5 generates better code than GPT and Gemini. GPT-generated JUnit test cases often fail, whereas Claude generates working test cases. 

Shape 

Development & Delivery Process 

Delivery Pipeline 

Stage 

Environment 

Activity 

1 

Local → Dev 

Developer pushes code 

2 

Dev 

QA testing 

3 

Dev 

UAT passed 

4 

Staging 

Stakeholder testing and approval 

5 

Release Branch 

PR merged after approval 

6 

Master 

Release branch merged 

7 

Production 

Final testing 

Release Cycle: 

Every Tuesday: New release 

Every Friday: Release scope finalized for upcoming Tuesday 

Parallel Development & Dependency Management 

